string_table: These options control WinRAR integration into Windows.
The first group of options allows to choose archive types to handle by WinRAR.
The second group selects places to add links to the WinRAR executable.
The last group controls integration into the Windows shell.
Shell integration provides handy features like "Extract" item in archive context menus, so usually there is no reason to disable it.
Press "Help" button to read the detailed description of these options.
You installed 32 bit WinRAR version on 64 bit Windows. You can get better performance and reliability by uninstalling 32 bit WinRAR and installing WinRAR x64.
You need to restart your computer to complete the installation.
